introduction
--------------------------------------

  welcome to another workbench toy.

  MystiCube opens a scalable window on the default pubscreen
  with a rotating, texture-mapped cube. you can drag'n'drop
  pictures on the cube's faces in order to display them.

  MystiCube works on all kinds of screen modes (including hi- and
  truecolor).

  press the 't' key for a frames-per-second counter.


requirements
--------------------------------------

  - OS3.0 (v39)
  - 68020
  - datatypes.library v39
  - guigfx.library v4
  - render.library v27

  supports
  
  - higher CPUs, FPU
  - OS3.1
  - CybergraphX, Picasso96


demonstrated features
--------------------------------------

  MystiCube is a quick hack to demonstrate some features of
  guigfx.library.

  - dynamic palette creation with a set of different pictures
  - screen-pen management
  - datatype loading
  - texture-mapping
  
  the source codes are included. feel free to cut'n'paste or
  modify whatever you want.

  guigfx.library is under development. updates, includes, and
  autodocs are available at the Binary Distillery support site:
  
  tek.flynet.de/binarydistillery/guigfx.html


